SIMPLE: een
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Een
<hw>E'en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>A contraction for
<xex>even</xex>. See <er>Even</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have <qex>e'en</qex> done with you.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Een</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Een
<hw>Een</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The old plural of
<er>Eye</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And eke with fatness swollen were his <qex>een</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>E'er</ent>⟦br⟧
